HEADWORD: Extrajudicial
<hw>Ex`tra*ju*di"cial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Out of or
beyond the power authority of a court or judge; beyond jurisdiction; not
valid as a part of a judicial proceeding; <as>as, <ex>extrajudicial</ex>
oaths, judgments, etc.</as>, are null and void.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Ex`tra*ju*di"cial*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extrajudicial conveyance</ent>⟦br⟧
